article.headline: Coward, Watts rally Eastern Washington over Montana State 108-104 in OT

images.name: Casey Jones' slam gets Eastern Washington fans hyped up
images.caption: Casey Jones attacks the rim with a hard slam to give Eastern Washington a two-point lead.

article.linkText: Coward, Watts rally Eastern Washington over Montana State 108-104 in OT
article.story: CHENEY, Wash. -- — Cedric Coward had 23 points and LeJuan Watts scored six of his 21 in overtime to rally Eastern Washington to a 108-104 victory over Montana State on Saturday night. Coward made two free throws and Watts followed with a layup for a 93-92 lead and the Eagles (20-10, 14-3 Big Sky Conference) never trailed again over the final 3:09 of the extra period. Coward added 10 rebounds for the Eagles (20-10, 14-3 Big Sky Conference). Watts made 8 of 11 shots and all four of his free throws. Jake Kyman scored 18 on 7-for-15 shooting. Eddie Turner III finished with 24 points, nine assists, eight rebounds and three steals for the Bobcats (13-17, 8-9). Brian Goracke added 22 points and eight rebounds. Robert Ford III scored 18. Turner hit a 3-pointer with eight seconds left, forcing overtime tied at 89. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
